<br>
Her priestess's had placed Gabrielle's wrapped body ontop of a platform sitting ontop of a pile of logs. Arround her body were different Herbs and flowers. The herbs given to Vasilissa De'Lerium were sprinkled over and under her death shroud.<br>
<br>
Around the unlit pyre, there stood 4 tourches, each in the proper direction of the North, South, West and East. The light casting eerie shadows along the snowcovered ground..<br>
<br>
In the wood, standing on pint, were Gabrielle's Sais. She did not know what to dowith them, or who to give them to. So she would wait to see who claimed them. More then liekly someone from her tribe.<br>
<br>
She took a dagger and slit an opening in her hand, taking her pointer finger on her other hand, she dipped it in and began to draw the sacred symbols on the wrappings.<br>
<br>
When she was through, she gave out the death cry, it was time to gather. She would wait in the shadows. <p>Dlasta &lt;&gt; Virgin Priestess of the Great Goddess Artemis&lt;&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasilissadelerium>Vasilissa De Lerium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa Apo Themiscrya</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#993300>(1/24/03 10:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=424.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/deleriuml9/images/del2.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Funeral for Gabrielle</span><hr size=1> She was sitting in her hut, putting on her warmest furs as she heard the death cry. She looked out the window at the falling snow. She wrapped her fur around her and left the hut, shutting the door behind her. Lukoi, her grey wolf, followed behind her. She walked the path to the sacred grove.<br>
<br>
