<br>
&quot;Tonight, Athelfi, we bid farewell to our Warrior Bard, Our Amazon Vasilissa Gabrielle. She has passed from this life, I am sure, to succedd in another.  Her lose came toa  shock to many o fus. I myself did not know her that well. But her stories and bardwork, were familiar to me. I have read much of her journies with Xena. At this time. I would like for anyone to come up, and say anything they would like about gabrielle, something to help us all, understand what we might not of known, for truly, we can not all know a person in the same way.&quot;<br>
<br>
She took a step back and let the procession go <p>Dlasta &lt;&gt; Virgin Priestess of the Great Goddess Artemis&lt;&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mysticlykastian>Mystic Lykastian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#993300>(1/27/03 11:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=424.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/magickalamzn/images/zoe.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A child's cry for her Mother...</span><hr size=1> A young amazon, no older than six, gulped down her fears and stepped out of the dark forest and into an opening, still far from her mother's body and the adult Amazons.  Zoe was tugging along behind her a young mare of the purest white.  She held a gold-colored rope which was tied around the horse's nose as best as her tiny hands could.  She was clad in a lose white dress with belled-out sleeves, tied languidly to her waist by a matching rope which twisted around her mare's nose.  Her bare feet, not used to Earth's harsh surface, were cut and bruised from the dreaded travel to visit her mother for the last time.<br>
<br>
The young Lykastian Princess was not ready for her mother to leave her.  Zoe was too inexperienced to the Amazon World around her, and now, she had no one.  Her blue orbs, puffed and reddened by the tears which fell and are still falling, looked upon her mother's body in the distance.<br>
<br>
She wished her shyness away, but wasn't granted that.  She wanted to step into the crowd and bid her mother a lasting prayer, or kiss, or something!  She wanted to see her mother!<br>
<br>
A soft nudge was felt on the back of her head and she turned around, placing her hand on the bottom of her mare's nose to comfort Sylver.  She closed her stinging eyes and rested her forehead across Sylver's bridge.  Soft sniffles breathed in cold air into her lungs.<br>
<br>
Her words were light and depressing, &quot;Sylvie...please bring mommy back.  I'm not ready to be out on my own.  I have no one now to care for me.&quot; Two tears rolled down her little flushed cheeks. &quot;My wings are not big enough to fly yet, I need my mommy...&quot;<br>
<br>
Sylver let out her regular snort, which sent a few of Zoe's locks behind her ears.  Her mare nudged her once again, pressing her to enter into the crowd.<br>
<br>
She turned, gulping once again, and tightly gripped Sylver's rope.  With closing her eyes once again, and opening them moments later, she began to make her way towards her mother's body. She stopped behind a few Amazons, still crying as every child would do when they lost their mommy. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Zoe</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, The mystic Lykastian Princess<br>
Daughter of the great battling bard, Gabrielle.<br>
</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amazonprincessriver>AmazonPrincessRiver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#993300>(1/28/03 11:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=424.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A child's cry for her Mother...</span><hr size=1> River, sensing her little sister's distress, made her way over to her.  She gave the girl a hug, then kneeled down slightly so their eyes were level.  Giving a sad smile, River wiped her sister's tears away gently.  <br>
<br>
&quot;I know it's hard, Zoe,&quot; she said quietly.  &quot;Your mommy was a great woman, and I can't replace her.  Wouldn't want to if I could.  But I am going to take care of you as best I can, okay?  Let's go up, and say our goodbyes.&quot;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 159<br> <font color=#993300>(1/28/03 12:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=424.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A child's cry for her Mother...</span><hr size=1> Alysia couldn't bare not being at her friend's funeral. A loud wolf cry was heard in mourning for the deceased as Alysia came walking through the crowd. Elea bowed her head in respect for her Queen. <br>
<br>
She wore short leathers and no boots. Tattoos adorning her body symbolizing her life. She looked down at her athelfi Gabrielle and whispered in ancient Tretmolec:<br>
<br>
~&quot; Death is never in vain when you've made a difference in the world. . .and in the Nation. &quot;~<br>
<br>
Alysia lowered her head lightly giving Gabrielle's spirit a blessing for safety in the world to come. She then sighed as she saw Zoe. She hadn't seen the little girl in some time now. But Alysia had always loved the little girl ever since Gabrielle came to Scynythia long ago, pregnant with the Amazon Princess. <br>
<br>
Aly nodded to River and placed a comforting hand on her shoulder. She then lowered herself to face Zoe where she whispered.<br>
<br>
&quot;If you ever need anything Zoe, you have your athelfi to rely on. And you may come to Scynthia whenever you wish child.&quot;<br>
<br>
She sighed lightly. She remembered long ago she had made a promise to Gabrielle. She would assist Zoe in training in the Shaman and other traits. She would not break her promise. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~*~ Jessica ~*~<br>
