<br>
She followed a little behind Alyisa, hearing only by word that Her grandmother was back, but...it was a time for mourning, not a time for celebration. She came up behind Alysia-Samsara and the child, placing a comforting hand on Aly's shoulder, not speaking. Aly had gone through alot these past few years. Losing her mother, then Wulf, and then just recently having to go through a trial. She knew all she and Belle would have to do was to be there for Aly and the rest of the Athelfi who loved Gabrielle. <br>
<br>
Odessa wasn't known to have much emotion, and she didn't have now. She was in sorrow than a fellow athelfi died, but the way she held herself never showed it. She truly was a strong Amazon. She whispered a silent prayer to the Atmah, and closed her eyes. She squeezed Aly's shoulder in a comforting way, letting here know she was there...<br>
<br>
